Do’s :

      1)Use a professional username and bio on platforms that show your college name.

      2)Share achievements, projects, and learning resources that build a positive online image.

      3)Think before posting or forwarding content; check whether it is respectful and genuine.

      4)Adjust privacy settings so that only trusted people see your personal information.

      5)Report and block abusive accounts instead of arguing in comments.

Don’ts:

       1)Do not post insulting or discriminatory memes about classmates, teachers, or communities.

       2)Do not share screenshots of private chats or emails without the other person’s permission.

       3)Do not share OTPs, passwords, UPI PINs, or bank details in messages or comments.

       4)Do not upload photos from college events that break rules or show unsafe behaviour.

       5)Do not comment using slang, threats, or abusive language on public posts.
